Description.LocalizedString: It’s a million yellow stripes to the next gig and you’ve got a bullet on two wheels to get you there. Even the roar of the engine can’t drown out the song in your head.
She remembered her initial experience performing at a vintage science fiction convention.
It was Kate’s first time in Japan and she was joining an iconic all-girl band for the performance of a lifetime.
There was still the illusion of safety then, as Kate wandered off alone with her guitar to the cave looming ahead.
Kate never missed a chance to sing at a festival, and she was prepared for Oktoberfest to be a raucous one.
Kate took the stage at a 50’s revival show and played till the cows came home.
After months touring, she pulled off on a Californian freeway and sauntered to the coast.
At first light, a little songbird landed on her windowsill and awoke her with music. She spent the rest of the day composing divine melodies.
She made plans with a special someone on Valentine's Day.
An ensemble she wore during her unannounced performance at a local pub.
She headed down South, back to her roots, to visit her family and get off the road for a while.
The outfit of a mysterious claimant from a lost realm.
Playing a concert during the lunar eclipse inspired Kate to add some theatrics to her set.
Her music appealed to the pop crowd, but she still stuck to her roots.
For a Halloween barn party, she thought she might pull a little prank on her friends and jump out of the crops.
She wore this ensemble while performing for a holiday benefit concert at her local community center.
NFA. If it was so, so it might be, and so it was. Zzl.
She used an electric guitar for the Sci-Fi Music gala.
She spent a peaceful evening by the fireplace, composing a new song.
A casual outfit for a fun day on the ranch. It is both practical and fashionable.
Lessens the likelihood of being pinched this St. Patrick’s Day. Sacrificed though? That might still happen.
She walked around the festival, enjoying the lively, bustling streets of the neighborhood.
